<Link id="l00186" /><CodeLine lineNumber="186"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Return the location for the register in \\a RegNum if there is a location.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00187" /><CodeLine lineNumber="187"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00188" /><CodeLine lineNumber="188"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// \\param RegNum the register number to find a location for.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00189" /><CodeLine lineNumber="189"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00190" /><CodeLine lineNumber="190"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// \\returns A location if one is available for \\a RegNum, or std::nullopt</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00192" /><CodeLine lineNumber="192" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarf/registerlocations/#a71d46b6c55ac8973987d21a7809ff271"><Highlight kind="normal">  std::optional&lt;UnwindLocation&gt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarf/registerlocations/#a71d46b6c55ac8973987d21a7809ff271">getRegisterLocation</a>(uint32&#95;t RegNum)</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword"> const </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">&#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00239" /><CodeLine lineNumber="239"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A class that represents a single row in the unwind table that is decoded by</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00240" /><CodeLine lineNumber="240"><Highlight kind="comment">/// parsing the DWARF Call Frame Information opcodes.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00241" /><CodeLine lineNumber="241"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00242" /><CodeLine lineNumber="242"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The row consists of an optional address, the rule to unwind the CFA and all</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00243" /><CodeLine lineNumber="243"><Highlight kind="comment">/// rules to unwind any registers. If the address doesn&#39;t have a value, this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00244" /><CodeLine lineNumber="244"><Highlight kind="comment">/// row represents the initial instructions for a CIE. If the address has a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00245" /><CodeLine lineNumber="245"><Highlight kind="comment">/// value the UnwindRow represents a row in the UnwindTable for a FDE. The</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00246" /><CodeLine lineNumber="246"><Highlight kind="comment">/// address is the first address for which the CFA location and register rules</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00247" /><CodeLine lineNumber="247"><Highlight kind="comment">/// are valid within a function.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00248" /><CodeLine lineNumber="248"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00249" /><CodeLine lineNumber="249"><Highlight kind="comment">/// UnwindRow objects are created by parsing opcodes in the DWARF Call Frame</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00250" /><CodeLine lineNumber="250"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Information and UnwindRow objects are lazily populated and pushed onto a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00251" /><CodeLine lineNumber="251"><Highlight kind="comment">/// stack in the UnwindTable when evaluating this state machine. Accessors are</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00252" /><CodeLine lineNumber="252"><Highlight kind="comment">/// needed for the address, CFA value, and register locations as the opcodes</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00253" /><CodeLine lineNumber="253"><Highlight kind="comment">/// encode a state machine that produces a sorted array of UnwindRow objects</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00254" /><CodeLine lineNumber="254"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\see UnwindTable.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00255" /><CodeLine lineNumber="255" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarf/unwindrow"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarf/unwindrow/#a4fb190f316b45043cb43eb55ec4638ec">UnwindRow</a> &#123;</Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
